        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:34PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 634 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kiahsville, or 14 miles southeast of Wayne, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kiahsville, Ranger, Gill, and Harts.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
